<subSubSection id="C353655E69717A26DDA8286007EBFCCB" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF636D569717A26DDA8286007EBFCCB" blockId="5.[163,1070,827,879]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Etymology: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: curved) refers to the shape of the ventral process of the aedeagus in lateral view.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C353655E69717A26DDA828DB0621FBE4" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF636D569717A26DDA828DB064BFC11" blockId="5.[163,1071,896,949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
Description: Body length 
<quantity id="4CB19B3069717A26DF2E28DB07E1FC32" box="[549,681,896,918]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" unit="mm" value="5.25" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="5.2">5.2-5.3 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 2.9-3.0 mm. Externally similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D5669717A26DC7228FB049CFC11" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[377,468,928,949]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC769717A26DC7228FB049CFC11" box="[377,468,928,949]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">R. rectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinguished as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF636D569717A26DDA8289D014CFC78" blockId="5.[163,1028,966,988]" box="[163,1028,966,988]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
Head (
<figureCitation id="13722A5069717A26DDED289D046BFC78" box="[230,291,966,988]" captionStart="Figs 8-12" captionStartId="6.[163,203,1060,1080]" captionTargetBox="[163,1046,197,1029]" captionTargetId="figure-210@6.[163,1098,197,1033]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 8-12: Rugilus curvatus nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11) aedeagus in lateral view; (12) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4507311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4507311/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) 1.06-1.08 times as broad as long; punctation less extensively confluent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF636D569717A26DDA828B60621FBE4" blockId="5.[163,1070,1004,1088]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
♂: sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="13722A5069717A26DC4C28B704CCFBA6" box="[327,388,1004,1026]" captionStart="Figs 8-12" captionStartId="6.[163,203,1060,1080]" captionTargetBox="[163,1046,197,1029]" captionTargetId="figure-210@6.[163,1098,197,1033]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 8-12: Rugilus curvatus nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11) aedeagus in lateral view; (12) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4507311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4507311/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) not distinctly modified; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="13722A5069717A26DE1928B70613FBA6" box="[786,859,1004,1026]" captionStart="Figs 8-12" captionStartId="6.[163,203,1060,1080]" captionTargetBox="[163,1046,197,1029]" captionTargetId="figure-210@6.[163,1098,197,1033]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 8-12: Rugilus curvatus nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11) aedeagus in lateral view; (12) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4507311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4507311/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) with not very deep, broadly V-shaped posterior excision; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13722A5069717A26DFA62F50066BFB85" box="[685,803,1035,1057]" captionStart="Figs 8-12" captionStartId="6.[163,203,1060,1080]" captionTargetBox="[163,1046,197,1029]" captionTargetId="figure-210@6.[163,1098,197,1033]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 8-12: Rugilus curvatus nov.sp.: (8) forebody; (9) male sternite VII; (10) male sternite VIII; (11) aedeagus in lateral view; (12) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 8: 1.0 mm; 9-12: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4507311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4507311/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Figs 11-12</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4CB19B3069717A26DE332F5006D1FB85" box="[824,921,1035,1057]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" unit="mm" value="0.65">0.65 mm</quantity>
long; ventral process strongly curved in lateral view, apically acute in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C353655E69717A26DDA82F0A05B1FADF" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF636D569717A26DDA82F0A05B1FADF" blockId="5.[163,1071,1105,1403]" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">
Comparative notes: As can be inferred from the similar external and male sexual characters, 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D5669717A26DC6A2F2B049EFB21" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[353,470,1136,1157]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvatus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC769717A26DC6A2F2B049EFB21" box="[353,470,1136,1157]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">R. curvatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D5669717A26DFAE2F2B0614FB20" baseAuthorityName="COIFFAIT" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[677,860,1135,1157]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridentatus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC769717A26DFAE2F2B0614FB20" box="[677,860,1135,1157]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">R. quadridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="498DF83769717A26DE672F340693FB21" box="[876,987,1135,1157]" country="Nepal" name="Dhawalagiri" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Dhaulagiri</collectingRegion>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D5669717A26D9132F2B0438FB00" authority="(Annapurna)" baseAuthorityName="Annapurna" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC769717A26D9132F2B05A9FB00" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">R. rectus</emphasis>
(Annapurna)
</taxonomicName>
. From the former, it is distinguished by the absence of a median posterior excision of the male sternite VII, the different shape of the posterior excision of the male sternite VIII, and by the differently shaped ventral process of the aedeagus. From the latter, it differs by the much shallower posterior excision of the male sternite VIII and by the much shorter and distinctly curved ventral process of the aedeagus. For additional characters separating it from 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D5669717A26DF6E2E730781FA99" box="[613,713,1320,1341]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC769717A26DF6E2E730781FA99" box="[613,713,1320,1341]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">R. rectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see the description above. For illustrations of the male sexual characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D5669717A26DF742E1C067FFAFF" baseAuthorityName="COIFFAIT" baseAuthorityYear="1975" box="[639,823,1350,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridentatus">
<emphasis id="B93DEAC769717A26DF742E1C067FFAFF" box="[639,823,1350,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">R. quadridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<figureCitation id="13722A5069717A26DE602E1D06E2FAF8" box="[875,938,1350,1372]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="4.[163,203,1098,1118]" captionTargetBox="[171,1067,199,1075]" captionTargetId="figure-251@4.[162,1069,197,1082]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-7: Rugilus rectus nov.sp. (1-6) and R. quadridentatus (COIFFAIT) (7): (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3, 7) male sternite VII; (4) male sternite VIII; (5) aedeagus in lateral view; (6) ventral process of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1-2: 1.0 mm; 3-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4507309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4507309/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="176">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
and 
